message:
refactor(build): Rename rust-core to wasm-compute and update build pipeline

Renames the Rust/WASM package from @phage/rust-core to @phage/wasm-compute
for clarity and updates all build infrastructure to match.

## Package Rename Rationale

The new name better reflects the package's purpose:
- **wasm-compute**: Clearly indicates WebAssembly computational utilities
- Not tied to Rust specifically (could theoretically use other WASM sources)
- Follows convention of describing output format, not source language

## .gitignore Updates

Added ignore patterns for new package:
```
packages/wasm-compute/target/
packages/wasm-compute/pkg/
packages/wasm-compute/node_modules/
```

## tsconfig.json Updates

Updated path aliases:
```json
"@phage/wasm-compute": ["packages/wasm-compute/pkg/wasm_compute.js"],
"@phage/wasm-compute/pkg/*": ["packages/wasm-compute/pkg/*"]
```

This allows importing from both the main entry point and specific
files within the pkg directory.

## scripts/build.ts Updates

Changed wasm-pack build command:
```typescript
// Before
await $`cd packages/rust-core && wasm-pack build --target nodejs`;
await $`bun run scripts/inline-wasm.ts`;

// After
await $`cd packages/wasm-compute && wasm-pack build --target nodejs --out-dir pkg`;
await $`bun run scripts/inline-wasm-compute.ts`;
```

Added explicit --out-dir pkg flag for consistency.

## scripts/inline-wasm-compute.ts (NEW)

Renamed and updated from inline-wasm.ts:
- Targets packages/wasm-compute/pkg directory
- Updates wasm_compute.js instead of rust_core.js
- Injects base64-encoded WASM bytes at top of file
- Patches default fallback to use inlined bytes

Key improvement: Patches the URL fallback directly:
```typescript
// Replaces:
if (typeof module_or_path === 'undefined') {
  module_or_path = new URL('wasm_compute_bg.wasm', import.meta.url);
}

// With:
if (typeof module_or_path === 'undefined') {
  module_or_path = wasmBytes;
}
```

This ensures inlined bytes are used even without explicit init().

## scripts/inline-wasm.ts (DELETED)

Removed the old script; functionality moved to inline-wasm-compute.ts.

## packages/comparison/package.json

Updated dependency:
```json
"dependencies": {
  "@phage-explorer/core": "workspace:*",
  "@phage/wasm-compute": "workspace:*"  // was @phage/rust-core
}
```

Note: There appears to be a duplicate opening brace in this file
that should be addressed separately.

## packages/comparison/src/edit-distance.ts

Updated WASM import and initialization:

```typescript
// Before
import { levenshtein_distance as wasmLevenshtein } from '@phage/rust-core';

// After
import initWasm, { initSync as initWasmSync, levenshtein_distance as wasmLevenshtein } from '@phage/wasm-compute/pkg/wasm_compute.js';

let wasmReady = false;
try {
  initWasmSync(undefined as unknown as { module: unknown });
  wasmReady = true;
} catch {
  initWasm().then(() => { wasmReady = true; }).catch(() => { wasmReady = false; });
}
```

The new initialization:
1. Tries synchronous init first (uses inlined bytes)
2. Falls back to async init if sync fails
3. Tracks ready state to avoid using WASM before initialized
4. Includes lazy re-init attempt in distance function

